<h3 id="getting-your-data">Getting your Data</h3>

<p>Once your customers have started signing-up, their data will appear in the guests report.</p>

<p>The default view shows all your records. If you want to see your custom fields, you can switch the splash page in the drop down menu.</p>

<p>In the guest‚Äôs page, you can view their details, usage history and leave some notes about the customer.</p>

<div class="mdl-typography--text-center">
  <img src="/images/community/tutorials/guest-lists.gif" width="400px" />
</div>

<h3 id="syncing-with-mailchimp-and-campaign-monitor">Syncing with MailChimp and Campaign Monitor</h3>

<p>To sync your emails with MailChimp, all you need to do is enable the newsletter in your splash page. Emails will automatically be sent to your service.</p>

<p>If you want to sync you custom fields with MailChimp, you need to be on a paid plan. If you‚Äôre on a paid plan, please make sure the ‚ÄòMerge Fieds‚Äô option is enabled. This only works with MailChimp at the moment.</p>

<div class="mdl-typography--text-center">
  <img src="/images/community/tutorials/registration-fields-merge-fields-mailchimp.png" width="800px" />
</div>

<h3 id="thats-a-wrap">That‚Äôs a Wrap</h3>

<p>You should be good to go, let us know if you need assistance with this!</p>

<h2 id="questions">Questions</h2>

<h3 id="what-if-they-turn-up-with-a-new-device">What if they turn up with a new device.</h3>

<p>If you‚Äôve selected ‚ÄúRequire Registration‚Äù, they will be able to sign-in with their chosen username and password.</p>

<p>If not, they will have to register again. There‚Äôs no way for us to tell who they are.</p>

<h3 id="i-cant-change-the-username">I can‚Äôt change the username</h3>

<p>That‚Äôs correct, the username field cannot be removed. The username is always the email of the customer.</p>

<h3 id="i-can-only-see-25-guests">I can only see 25 guests</h3>

<p>On the free plan, the number of guests you can view is limited to 25.</p>

<h3 id="i-dont-see-my-custom-fields-in-mailchimp">I don‚Äôt see my custom fields in MailChimp</h3>

<p>This option is only available for paid plan. If you‚Äôre on a paid plan, first check you have enabled ‚ÄúMerge Registration Fields‚Äù in your portal.</p>

<p>If you‚Äôre sure you‚Äôve done this, check your field IDs match. Your fields ID are set in MailChimp. Your merge ID must match your Unique ID:</p>

<div class="row">
  <div class="small-12 medium-6 columns">
    <img src="/images/community/tutorials/mailchimp-merge-fields.png" width="100%" />
  </div>
  <div class="small-12 medium-6 columns">
    <img src="/images/community/tutorials/mailchimp-merge-2.png" width="100%" />
  </div>
</div>

<h3 id="i-deleted-a-field-my-data-looks-wrong">I deleted a field, my data looks wrong.</h3>

<p>We recommend you don‚Äôt delete fields if you already have data. If you want to change some fields, it‚Äôs best to create a new splash page.</p>

<h3 id="can-i-export-the-data">Can I export the data</h3>

<p>You bet! Simply visit your reports page and hit the download button. You‚Äôll be able to download the data as a CSV. Please note, this is a paid feature.</p>

